description: RA is a chronic autoimmune disease that causes inflammation in the joints. It can also affect other parts of the body, such as the lungs, heart, and eyes. description: Scleroderma is a rare autoimmune disease that causes the skin and connective tissues to thicken and harden. It can also affect the internal organs, such as the lungs, heart, and kidneys. description: HUS is a rare but serious condition that can occur after an infection or other illness. It causes damage to the tiny blood vessels in the kidneys, which can lead to kidney failure. HUS can be life-threatening and requires immediate medical attention.

description: Evans syndrome is a rare autoimmune disorder characterized by the simultaneous occurrence of immune thrombocytopenic purpura (ITP) and autoimmune hemolytic anemia (AIHA).
